courses.learning_outcomes:
Students would be able to:
1) understand how various country institutions such as the political economy, legal systems and social norms shape the corporate governance and accounting systems across countries;
2) analyze how firms’ corporate governance and accounting systems, which are shaped by their own country institutions, operate across countries;
3) identify the challenges and analyze the effectiveness of corporate governance and accounting systems of listed firms across countries, with a focus on Asia and China.

Students will be able to:
1. have a broad understanding of the recent FinTech development;
2. have hands-on and problem solving experiences on FinTech applications and innovation.

Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:
a. Take innovation policy from theory to practice;
b. Cultivate individual’s innovative mind set from within and without;
c. Conduct effective innovation management

Through the design, organization and implementation of a field study, students will be able to:
- acquire awareness of, and an appreciation for, the diversity and complexity of the international business environment;
- understand the role of analysis of macro dimensions (cultural, demographic, economic, educational, environmental, legal, political, sociological and technological) in making global business decisions;
- review contemporary and relevant developments in the global or regional arena, and to explore the possible strategic alternatives to capitalize on changes in the global scenario;
- apply business/ management concepts and skills acquired during the doctoral program in a real-life global business context; and
- generate insightful and concrete business plans based on the research findings of the field study.

Students will be able to:
1. have a systematic review of monetary policy making in major central banks (e.g., the Federal Reserve and the People's Bank of China);
2. gain insights on the latest development of macro financial issues in China;
3. understand the interactions of these new developments within the global financial system.

Students will:
- be able to understand the theories, principles and practices of risk management and insurance;
- understand how corporate risk managers are dealing with risks and arranging insurance policies;
- be familiar with risk management and insurance innovations and some current insurance issues around the world.

Students will:
- be familiar with the foundations underpinning investment/trading decisions;
- have thorough understanding of the psychology of trading, market liquidity, macroeconomic investment strategies, momentum and contrarian trading strategies, market volatility, technical analysis;
- be familiar with empirical financial market regularities and practical applications.
